com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting
Class ScriptPropertyAccess

java.lang.Object
  com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.ScriptPropertyAccess

public class ScriptPropertyAccess
extends java.lang.Object

Scripting class to check or retrieve property values for use in scripts. Properties are searched for in the Step, Job, Build Request, Source Config, Workflow, Build Life, Build Process Request, Project and then System scope. This class is exposed as 'properties' in any pre-condition or notification script.

Examples:

To retrieve the value of a named property and compare it to a expected value: 

    properties.get('os') == 'windows'
      - or -
    properties.equals('os', 'windows')
To see if a named property with a non-blank, non-null value: 
    properties.has('os')
      - or -
    properties.isBlank('os')
To see if a named multi-valued property has an expected value as one of its values: 
    properties.containsValue('os', 'windows')

containsValue

public boolean containsValue(java.lang.String propName,
                             java.lang.String value)
This method will determine if the value of the property is equal to the expected value. If the value is multi-valued, it checks if it is equal to one of the values. This can be used with properties that have comma-separated values such as multi-select properties.

Parameters:
propName - The name of the property to check the value of.
value - The value which may or may not be associated with the multi-valued property.
Returns:
true if the value is the property value or one of the property values, else false
